se xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 27, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104nlx1665702616810.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nlx1665702616810.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nlx1665702616810.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"nlx1665702616810\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Enables or disables the session panel, and controls its position.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"nlx1665702616810__topic_d146852e1_d146853e1_d146854e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nlx1665702616810__p_d146855e1_d146856e1_d146857e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">PanelType</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">On</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">No</code>|<code class=\"ph codeph\">Top</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">Left</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">Bottom</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">Right</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph defvalue\">Floating</code> |</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section table\" id=\"nlx1665702616810__section_w3442ab1b5b3_w3443ab1b5_w3444ab1\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"nlx1665702616810__table_d17993e1_d17994e1_d17995e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Default value</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">Floating</code>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">File section</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yzj1665702614359.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yzj1665702614359.html\" title=\"The [upi] section of the initialization file determines the appearance or behavior of many Universal Presentation Interface (UPI) objects under Microsoft Windows.\">[upi]</a></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"nlx1665702616810__section_oyy_5r1_zvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d853977e125\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">When <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">PanelType</span> is set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">No</code>, the session panel is\n            disabled and cannot be shown or hidden using the ^ATTRIBUTE structure editor function\n               (<span class=\"ph keypress\">Gold X</span>). To enable the session panel, set it to any\n            of the other values.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">If the setting is not present, the session panel is displayed as a floating panel.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"nlx1665702616810__note_hqv_wr1_zvb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> In the default Uniface installation,\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">PanelType</span> in <span class=\"ph filepath\">usys.ini</span> is set to\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">No</code>.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yqt1665703084374.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Panels</a></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/oat1665702714863.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Session Panel</a><p>Specifies a panel that is available for the duration of the application session, even if a panel has been specified for the current component, or a toolbar definition exists.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530318\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530318\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "PanelType Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 27, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Enables or disables the session panel, and controls its position. PanelType = On | No | Top | Left | Bottom | Right | Floating | Default value Floating File section [upi] Description When PanelType is set to No , the session panel is disabled and cannot be shown or hidden using the ^ATTRIBUTE structure editor function ( Gold X ). To enable the session panel, set it to any of the other values. If the setting is not present, the session panel is displayed as a floating panel. Note: In the default Uniface installation, PanelType in usys.ini is set to No . Related Links Panels Session Panel Specifies a panel that is available for the duration of the application session, even if a panel has been specified for the current component, or a toolbar definition exists. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}